    <briefdescription>
<para>Direct alphabet (also identity alphabet or integer alphabet) using integers as symbols. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>This alphabet presumes that all integers are valid symbols. Therefore, calling member functions <ref refid="classmata_1_1IntAlphabet_1ac49a8b966d82d52bec89a62be2e913b5" kindref="member">get_complement()</ref> and <ref refid="classmata_1_1IntAlphabet_1a3c0c3020b65d29e54dcd8baeea4e87ec" kindref="member">get_alphabet_symbols()</ref> makes no sense in this context and the methods will throw exceptions warning about the inappropriate use of <ref refid="classmata_1_1IntAlphabet" kindref="compound">IntAlphabet</ref>. If one needs these functions, they should use <ref refid="classmata_1_1OnTheFlyAlphabet" kindref="compound">OnTheFlyAlphabet</ref> instead of <ref refid="classmata_1_1IntAlphabet" kindref="compound">IntAlphabet</ref>. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
